September 1307":"6 september 1307","1290":"1290","England":"England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England","England, United Kingdom":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1255–6 September 1307":"1255–6 September 1307","1250–1301":"1250–1301","1279–1355":"1279–1355","1255–1307":"1255–1307","before 4 March 1301":"before 4 March 1301","before 1279":"before 1279","1259":"1259","1279":"1279","1301":"1301","1355":"1355","1255":"1255","Bef 1279":"before 1279","1250":"1250","1307":"1307","6 September 1307":"6 September 1307","1290":"1290","England":"England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Isolde","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The name of the tragic mistress of Tristan in the Arthurian romances. There are several versions of the story. The main features are that the beautiful Isolde, an Irish princess, is betrothed to the aged King Mark of Cornwall. However, through accidentally drinking a magic potion, she and the young Cornish knight Tristan fall in love, with tragic consequences. The story has exercised a powerful hold on the European imagination. The name was relatively common in Britain in the Middle Ages, but is much rarer today."],"variants":[{"name":"Isolda","meanings":["The name of the tragic mistress of Tristan in the Arthurian romances. There are several versions of the story. The main features are that the beautiful Isolde, an Irish princess, is betrothed to the aged King Mark of Cornwall. However, through accidentally drinking a magic potion, she and the young Cornish knight Tristan fall in love, with tragic consequences. The story has exercised a powerful hold on the European imagination. The name was relatively common in Britain in the Middle Ages, but is much rarer today."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":4,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between